Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.59,0:00:04.89,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Encounters are mysterious!\NBut the world is even more so!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.89,0:00:07.03,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I'm so glad I'm with you!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.03,0:00:10.27,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Today's all deduction!\NLet's{\rHonorifics - Narration Off\be10} chan{\r\be10}ge our view of people sometimes!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.27,0:00:11.97,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}He sees the single truth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.97,0:00:13.87,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}and looks like a kid but has the mind of an adult.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.87,0:00:16.22,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.42,0:01:41.53,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Thanks to Ran's plan to bring her parents back together,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.53,0:01:44.66,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}we came to a midsummer beach.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.66,0:01:50.93,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}But a girl we met fell into critical condition after a sea snake bit her.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.94,0:01:57.27,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}This was no accident! It's a criminal act disguised as an accident!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.79,0:02:08.25,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Izu\NQueen Hotel
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.95,0:02:11.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What? Bring her insurance card to the hospital right away?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.05,0:02:14.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The hospital staff says it'd be best to have it,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.86,0:02:18.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,plus I feel all alone...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.06,0:02:23.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Kiwako always takes it when traveling, so it should be somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.00,0:02:26.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But never mind that! How is she?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.80,0:02:30.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She's still in the Intensive Care Unit.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.74,0:02:32.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I think her condition's gotten worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.64,0:02:38.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The doctors keep rushing in and out, but they won't tell me anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.08,0:02:40.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think she might die?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.52,0:02:43.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You idiot! What kind of crap is that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.32,0:02:48.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll get her insurance card and be right there! Just wait quietly!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.73,0:02:52.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You and Kiwako are in the same room, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.16,0:02:53.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.10,0:02:58.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh no! The card key is still in the room!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.27,0:03:02.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I forgot it when she asked me to get a bath towel from our room.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.61,0:03:04.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What do we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.04,0:03:06.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It locks automatically, so we can't get inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.88,0:03:08.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sheesh.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.61,0:03:14.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll call the front desk from our room and have 'em bring a spare key.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.52,0:03:20.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, that's right. Room 406. Yes. Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.42,0:03:24.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks. Sorry for the bother.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.63,0:03:27.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.86,0:03:30.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What is it, kid? Don't scare me like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.67,0:03:36.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You all went scuba diving around noon, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.17,0:03:36.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.91,0:03:40.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you catch anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.11,0:03:41.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Like fish.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.28,0:03:44.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I didn't get anything this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.38,0:03:46.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What about the others?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.15,0:03:47.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I dunno.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.82,0:03:51.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We're familiar with these waters, and we all did our own thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.62,0:03:55.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so I'm not sure who did what.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.43,0:03:58.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I think Masahiko and Kiwako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} wore matching wetsuits
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.73,0:04:01.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and did their diving at the same spot, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.50,0:04:03.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,They're really close!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.17,0:04:08.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Them and Hiroshi are all childhood friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.10,0:04:12.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,They've always had fun together, since they were kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.34,0:04:14.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,They're all classmates?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.18,0:04:17.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, Hiroshi and Masahiko are the same age as me,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.45,0:04:22.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but Kiwako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} is one year younger, the same age as Harumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.99,0:04:29.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,To be honest, I planned to quit this club my second year of college.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.06,0:04:33.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But I{\rHonorifics - Dialogue} chan{\r}ged my mind when Kiwako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}'s group joined.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.36,0:04:35.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess it was love at first sight.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.07,0:04:39.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.67,0:04:44.81,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}How stupid! Why am I telling all this to a kid?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.81,0:04:46.78,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Wait a minute!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.78,0:04:49.58,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Does that mean...?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.58,0:04:53.52,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}That person and that person... Could it be?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.25,0:05:00.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,- There you are.\N- Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.76,0:05:02.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.03,0:05:09.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Insurance card, insurance card...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.50,0:05:15.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Geez! Here's where you left it!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.54,0:05:20.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,- I assume this is your card key?\N- Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.51,0:05:26.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you help me? I can't find Kiwako's insurance card.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.08,0:05:29.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Did she maybe forget it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.55,0:05:33.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Inside the towel at the bottom of the bag.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.86,0:05:36.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Just look.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.93,0:05:39.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The towel at the bottom of the bag...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.26,0:05:44.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,H-Here it is! How did you know?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.80,0:05:48.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,My grandmother taught it to me when I was a kid, and I taught them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.91,0:05:52.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's childhood friends for ya!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.71,0:05:56.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not the only one. Masahiko knows it, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.18,0:06:02.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, Detective. You have a car, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.09,0:06:04.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. It's a rental.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.25,0:06:09.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then could you drive us three to the hospital?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.13,0:06:11.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, no problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.49,0:06:13.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then let me come, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.86,0:06:16.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm worried about Kiwako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.67,0:06:20.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be stupid. Five people can't fit in that tiny car.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.50,0:06:22.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.37,0:06:27.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's all right. I can drop her off at the hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.84,0:06:31.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What are those suitcases for, Mom?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.71,0:06:36.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you can't tell? As soon as I drop you off, I'm going home.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.65,0:06:38.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.32,0:06:42.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want to share the same space with this lunkhead anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.46,0:06:45.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,- Hey, Eri.\N- What?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.40,0:06:47.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We need to talk later.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.23,0:06:52.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? What about? I can't wait to find out.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.34,0:06:54.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.14,0:07:03.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You're going too fast, Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.41,0:07:09.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sheesh. You don't have to sulk because he didn't notice your ring.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.15,0:07:12.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not the ring. It's the incident.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.09,0:07:13.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The incident?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.36,0:07:19.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Not everything adds up yet, but this is clearly a murder case.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.43,0:07:21.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Murder?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.83,0:07:25.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And I'm angry at him for not even realizing it!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.27,0:07:31.51,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Yes. It's a murder case, and I have an idea who's responsible.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.51,0:07:34.31,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}There's just one thing I don't understand...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.31,0:07:38.68,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Why did that person do that then?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.68,0:07:41.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What could it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.58,0:07:45.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,- Do you mean the incident?\N- No, what he wants to tell me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.99,0:07:48.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He said we have to talk later.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.32,0:07:49.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.66,0:07:56.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Divorce... Custody rights... Or perhaps...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.20,0:07:57.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mom...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.60,0:08:04.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's probably nothing at all. He's only testing me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.91,0:08:07.01,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Testing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.01,0:08:08.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's always the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.28,0:08:12.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He gets me worked up and then watches me squirm.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.12,0:08:14.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He's so self-conceited!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.25,0:08:18.05,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Now I see! So that's what the deal is!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.05,0:08:23.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ran. Sorry, but I can't stand it anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.43,0:08:25.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.20,0:08:34.86,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}No question about it! That person is behind this!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.60,0:08:41.56,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,West Izu Hospital
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.54,0:08:41.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Masahiko! I brought it!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.56,0:08:43.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Kiwako's insurance card!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.78,0:08:44.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.88,0:08:48.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,- So, how's her condition?!\N- How is she, Brother?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.79,0:08:53.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know. She's still in the ICU.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.89,0:08:57.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me know when you find out how she is.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.26,0:09:02.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You're leaving, Mom?! But Dad said he has to talk with you!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.57,0:09:07.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Talk? Do I really need to lend my ear to that lady-killer?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.87,0:09:11.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, really?! You're fans of mine?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.58,0:09:13.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.34,0:09:18.48,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}What a lost cause. Maybe I should give the guy a hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.48,0:09:20.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,- Say, Nurse.\N- Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.92,0:09:23.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I have a favor to ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.72,0:09:28.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, Mom! He can't help it! He's famous!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.39,0:09:34.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He's all smiles at a time like this! I've had enough of his callousness!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.60,0:09:37.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But that's because...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.53,0:09:47.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Paging Eri Kisaki and Harumi Matsuzaki from the Queen Hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.21,0:09:50.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Please come to the hospital director's office immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.65,0:09:53.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,- Kogoro Mouri is waiting.\N- Alright!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.88,0:09:55.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Me?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.99,0:10:03.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,- Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!\N- Are you okay?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.53,0:10:06.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait! Little boy!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.86,0:10:09.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry! I'll bring it right back!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.98,0:10:15.69,Dialogue Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"Director"
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.34,0:10:15.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you call us here like that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.11,0:10:19.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If you have something to tell me, just say it already!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.48,0:10:21.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mom...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.01,0:10:22.65,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Yikes...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.65,0:10:26.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Umm, I can come back later if I'm in the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.05,0:10:28.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm concerned about Kiwako, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.32,0:10:31.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So you {\i1}are{\i0} concerned about her?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.46,0:10:33.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Can't say I blame you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.16,0:10:38.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,After all, the difference between murder and attempted murder hangs in the balance.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.76,0:10:41.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. That wasn't an accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.87,0:10:46.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was a premeditated act meant to kill.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.37,0:10:51.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone purposely had the sea snake bite Kiwako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.91,0:10:55.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Harumi Matsuzaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}... That someone was you!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.85,0:10:59.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,- You can't be serious!\N- The fang marks.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.45,0:11:00.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Fang marks?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.92,0:11:03.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sea snakes have rather small heads.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.82,0:11:08.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If one bit a human, it'd be somewhere small, like a fingertip.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.66,0:11:12.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yet, Kiwako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s fang marks were on the back of her hand,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.33,0:11:15.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,where a sea snake couldn't have bitten her.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.13,0:11:21.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,When rushing to help, she held the head of the snake she had hidden,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.41,0:11:26.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,forced its mouth open, and had it bite down as if it had attached.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.28,0:11:29.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that right, Harumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.45,0:11:34.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. You pretended to play dumb but actually saw through it all.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.75,0:11:37.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then tell us this, Great Detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.65,0:11:41.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,How can you be sure it was Harumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.09,0:11:44.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Couldn't any of the others have done it too?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.83,0:11:49.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, it was by sheer{\rHonorifics - Dialogue} chan{\r}ce that Kiwako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} started to drown.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.60,0:11:53.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And what if it {\i1}wasn't{\i0} by{\rHonorifics - Dialogue} chan{\r}ce?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.74,0:11:57.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What if Kiwako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had done it on purpose?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.31,0:12:00.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,On purpose? What for?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.18,0:12:04.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's natural for lovers to want to know the other's true feelings.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.62,0:12:09.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,To arouse the other's interest, one might get close to another person,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.42,0:12:13.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,or even purposely not wear a wedding ring...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.06,0:12:15.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, you're saying Kiwako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.73,0:12:17.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.13,0:12:23.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Kiwako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} pretended to drown to test Masahiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, her fiancé.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.00,0:12:27.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,To see if he would come to her rescue, even though he can't swim.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.94,0:12:35.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,As proof, she murmured this after confirming that he tried to help...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.68,0:12:37.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"That's a relief..."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.68,0:12:43.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But they're getting married next week. Why do that now?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.82,0:12:47.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She wanted to be extra sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.09,0:12:51.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She was irritated that her fiancé didn't even bat an eye
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.60,0:12:54.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,when she clung to this famous celebrity.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.30,0:13:00.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And then she executed the fake drowning plan they made in advance.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.30,0:13:01.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"They"?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.84,0:13:04.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Two people.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.14,0:13:11.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,For the plan to work, someone had to tell Masahiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.18,0:13:17.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It'd be a disgrace if someone else on the beach rescued her first.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.85,0:13:22.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And that other person was you, Harumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.69,0:13:27.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The signal for the start of the plan was probably when she said...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.80,0:13:32.17,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Could you get a fresh beach towel from our room?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.17,0:13:34.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Or so I'd assume. After that...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.64,0:13:37.91,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Later, Harumi! Don't forget!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.91,0:13:42.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,...Is something else she said, so that sounds about right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.21,0:13:47.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But Harumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} tried to stop her from going into the water!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.35,0:13:52.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, she wouldn't have done that in front of a famous detective!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.02,0:13:56.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's {\i1}why{\i0} she tried to stop her. Because I was right there watching.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.09,0:14:00.10,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}You don't have to do it today. Can't you go tomorrow?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.10,0:14:02.17,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I'll be fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.17,0:14:06.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But Kiwako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} continued with the plan anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.44,0:14:12.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Unaware that Harumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had another, more sinister plan in store.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.21,0:14:14.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You can't be serious...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.48,0:14:17.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Upon returning to her room to get the bath towel,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.88,0:14:21.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Harumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} concealed her sea snake in her pouch
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.22,0:14:25.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and went back to the seaside restaurant.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.42,0:14:32.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, at the proper time, she signaled Kiwako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} to falsely drown.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.66,0:14:34.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, when rushing to help with everyone else,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.93,0:14:41.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,she took out the hidden sea snake and had it bite Kiwako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.84,0:14:44.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But what's your plan, Great Detective?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.91,0:14:50.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The murder weapon is gracefully swimming in the Pacific Ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.35,0:14:54.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Without a weapon, this case won't stand up in court.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.48,0:14:59.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I already told you. She placed the sea snake in her waist pouch.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.89,0:15:04.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's more, whether out of confidence or confusion,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.59,0:15:07.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,she never left our side after the incident.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.60,0:15:12.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It should still be there in her pouch:
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.20,0:15:16.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,adhesive tape with black-banded sea krait scales still attached!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.81,0:15:18.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,- Tape?\N- Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.64,0:15:24.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Simply stuffing it in would make it seem unnatural when taking it out,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.08,0:15:27.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and there'd be a{\rHonorifics - Dialogue} chan{\r}ce it could bite her fingers instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.05,0:15:33.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She most likely taped the snake down in several spots in the pouch
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.32,0:15:36.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and left only the snake's head sticking out.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.76,0:15:41.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That way, she could pull it out and have it bite in an instant.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.93,0:15:46.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then the feather-like things I saw on the snake were...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.30,0:15:48.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Probably some of the tape.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.67,0:15:53.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The rest of the tape is probably still inside her pouch.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.28,0:15:55.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Inside her pouch?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.55,0:15:59.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But we still don't know for sure she put a snake in...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.32,0:16:03.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We do. Because of her card key.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.32,0:16:07.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,As soon as I saw her compact, wallet, and everything
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.02,0:16:10.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,on top of the card key she left in the room, it hit me
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.69,0:16:15.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,that she might've emptied her pouch and put something else in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.73,0:16:20.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But why would she harm Kiwako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?! She's her brother's fiancée!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.84,0:16:24.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This is purely speculation,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.21,0:16:31.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but I wonder if Harumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} might've liked Masahiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.05,0:16:35.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No... loved him. A lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.29,0:16:39.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be silly, Dad! She and Masahiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} are brother and sister!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.79,0:16:43.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No. They probably aren't.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.03,0:16:50.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If they were, all four in their group would've been childhood friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.57,0:16:54.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Especially given that she's the same age as Kiwako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.30,0:16:58.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then they're step-siblings from when their parents remarried?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.31,0:17:00.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Probably.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.34,0:17:05.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Seeing as Hiroshi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} calls her "{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}" even though she's younger,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.72,0:17:09.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,they were probably in college when it happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.15,0:17:12.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No. It was my second year in high school
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.59,0:17:18.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,when my mom remarried and I first met Masahiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.13,0:17:23.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He's a little helpless but nice, and I fell for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.47,0:17:27.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I never had anyone like him around me before.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.04,0:17:31.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But Kiwako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was always by his side.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.27,0:17:37.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Whenever she spoke about his childhood, I'd get very sad and angry.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.61,0:17:43.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was like she was saying, "You don't know {\i1}anything{\i0} about him!"
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.49,0:17:49.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,My only choice was to hide my feelings and call him my brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.69,0:17:54.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Their sudden engagement and marriage was a huge shock.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.83,0:18:00.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,To top it all off, she came to me with that plan, knowing how I felt.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.00,0:18:03.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Almost as if she was mocking me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.11,0:18:07.54,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}- Pretending to drown?\N- Please? Can you do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.54,0:18:09.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And then you devised your own plan?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.85,0:18:11.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.58,0:18:16.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't want to hand Masahiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} over to her! So I...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.92,0:18:19.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So I...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.36,0:18:27.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so stupid, aren't I? Doing that would only make him sad...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.40,0:18:31.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm really so stupid...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.24,0:18:38.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You're Kiwako Toda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s friends, correct?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.61,0:18:44.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We managed to administer an antitoxin just in time!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.18,0:18:46.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A few more days and she'll be just fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.82,0:18:49.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's all thanks to your emergency treatment!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.19,0:18:50.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was nothing!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.52,0:18:52.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's wonderful news, Kiwako!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.69,0:18:54.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,W-Where's Harumi?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.52,0:18:57.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She's here! Harumi!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.00,0:19:09.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,C'mon! Why so bashful?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.67,0:19:12.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.41,0:19:17.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't know how you felt...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.95,0:19:25.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I had no idea, until I saw your serious look when you rushed to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.79,0:19:27.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Kiwako...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.96,0:19:34.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yet, I asked you for that favor... I'm really sorry! I regret it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.40,0:19:42.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you saying?! I tried to... I tried to...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.54,0:19:45.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,W-Wait! Did something happen?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.01,0:19:55.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's nothing. I was punished for testing the heart of another.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.09,0:19:58.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why a sea snake bit me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.12,0:20:03.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.93,0:21:36.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That was amazing detective work again, Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.90,0:21:40.44,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Sometimes I can't remember anything at all...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.44,0:21:44.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Plus, it sounds like you noticed what Mom did.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.14,0:21:49.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? Noticing but pretending not to know is all the worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.42,0:21:50.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.98,0:21:54.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,- What's she talking about?\N- Look at you playing dumb again!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.65,0:21:57.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,- She's talking about the ring!\N- Ring?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.59,0:21:59.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that's...!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.29,0:22:01.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.63,0:22:03.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You mean this?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.06,0:22:06.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.83,0:22:12.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I found it under the beach umbrella you were using.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.34,0:22:17.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,How did you know I lost my ring there?!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.11,0:22:23.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be stupid. Nobody dries their hair with their glasses on.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.75,0:22:27.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That was evidence you were looking for something.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.59,0:22:34.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,People really only lose contacts, earrings, and rings on beaches.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.36,0:22:38.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So the{\rHonorifics - Dialogue} san{\r}d on your knees was because you were looking for the ring!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.97,0:22:42.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I get it! You wanted to tell her about the ring!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.37,0:22:45.74,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The old guy did notice!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.74,0:22:50.08,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Geez. If only he was always that sharp.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.08,0:22:52.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, could you be any more obvious?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.98,0:22:57.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Drinking tea with your left hand, wringing your hands nervously...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.35,0:22:59.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't help it...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.39,0:23:02.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Kogoro Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.99,0:23:04.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hi!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.23,0:23:15.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad! Hey, Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.17,0:23:18.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mom! Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.34,0:23:21.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.01,0:23:24.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright! Next time for sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.58,0:23:27.91,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}It'll never, ever happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.75,0:23:46.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,They match perfectly!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.35,0:23:52.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder why. The ones in Chapters 1 through 6 are all slightly off.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.32,0:23:55.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He obviously copied an earlier signature.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.53,0:23:57.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Why would he do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.43,0:24:01.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Because he didn't want to write it anymore...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.33,0:24:03.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,...or he couldn't anymore?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.13,0:24:08.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That means Shinmei{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r} might already be dead, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.07,0:24:14.03,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.03,0:24:19.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan's Hint: "Halves at the Top"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.04,0:24:20.87,Dialogue Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time is the mystery of a mystery writer!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.87,0:24:22.95,Dialogue Top,,0000,0000,0000,,The best mysteries are the mysterious ones!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.95,0:24:23.65,Dialogue Top,,0000,0000,0000,,You said it!
